cs.LG, cs.DM, cs.SI, cs.AI, cs.CC

The paper deals with a machine learning problem of ranking items based on pairwise preferences, which falls under the category of supervised learning. The use of graph structure and locality assumption suggests that the paper may belong to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Among these, cs.LG is the most likely category as the paper proposes a new algorithm for ranking based on an SVM approach and provides statistical consistency analysis. The use of graph structure and chromatic number also suggests that the paper may be relevant to cs.DM and cs.SI. The focus on machine learning and algorithm design suggests that the paper may also be relevant to cs.AI. The analysis of sample complexity and comparison with fundamental limits suggests that the paper may be relevant to cs.CC.
